comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure.  GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 600 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2). Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels) All prints perfect. Transferred into DPBS, then tried to roll but gap was too big and gels didn't roll around bar properly. Stored in DPBS, in fridge for further measurement of height.

Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure.  GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 600 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2). Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels) 5 perfect prints, 1 with air bubble in first layer -> discarded, 1 fell down during rolling. Prints quite stiff -- hard to roll. Cooling of gluing ink was better - gap still quite big- 4 prints r&g. Then stored in DPBS before transferring all at the same time into separate 24-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S (221126MF)
